Package: dsVert
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Server-Side Functions for Vertically Partitioned Data
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Sarrat González", email = "david.sarrat@isglobal.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Miron", "Banjac", email = "miron.banjac@isglobal.org",
           role = "ctb"),
    person("Juan R", "González", email = "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org",
           role = "ctb")
  )
Description: Server-side DataSHIELD functions for privacy-preserving analysis
    of vertically partitioned federated data. Implements ECDH-PSI record alignment
    (P-256 elliptic curve private set intersection), Multiparty Homomorphic
    Encryption (MHE) with threshold decryption for cross-server correlation, and
    Block Coordinate Descent for Generalized Linear Models. All methods preserve
    data privacy by ensuring raw data never leaves the server.
